rendition.
Description: supplies information about the rendition or appearance of one or more elements in the source text.
Attributes: scope (where CSS is used, provides a way of defining); selector (contains a selector or series of selectors specifying the elements to which the contained style description applies, expressed in the language specified in the)
Examples: display: block; | font-style: italic; | text-align: center;
        font-size: small;
        font-size: large;
        font-size: xx-large
Class membership: att.global, att.styleDef

style definition language declaration.
Description: specifies the name of the formal language in which style or renditional information is supplied elsewhere in the document. The specific version of the scheme may also be supplied.
Examples: font-weight: bold;
        font-style: italic;
Class membership: att.global, att.declarable, att.styleDef, model.encodingDescPart

formal language.
Description: contains literal code from some formal language such as a programming language.
Attributes: lang (a name identifying the formal language in which the code is expressed.)
Examples: Size fCheckbox1Size = new Size();
       fCheckbox1Size.Height = 500;
       fCheckbox1Size.Width = 500;
       xCheckbox1.setSize(fCheckbox1Size);
Class membership: att.global, model.emphLike

Description: describes the rendering or appearance intended for all occurrences of an element in a specified context for a specified type of output.
Attributes: scope (provides a way of defining)
Examples: font-style: italic;


        left-margin: 2em;
Class membership: att.global, model.oddDecl
